  "datePublished": "2026-01-01",
  "description": "A sample is a subset of a population selected for observation. Statistics exists because populations are usually too large, too expensive, or too impractical to observe in full. You cannot measure the blood pressure of every human alive, but you can measure the blood pressure of 500 people and use the results to draw conclusions about the whole. The 500 people are the sample; the conclusions about all humans are the inference.\n",
